    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The [auth spec](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/v1.0.0-alpha.7/src/engine/authentication.md) defines how the a `--jwt-secret` CLI flag works. I understand this to be from an EL perspective and therefore not directly applicable to a CL.\r\n\r\n### Proposal\r\n\r\nLH has *multiple ELs*, so we need to figure out how to have secrets for each. Thankfully, don't need to support *unauthenticated* ELs anymore.\r\n\r\nI propose we add the following CLI flag to the BN:\r\n\r\n- `--execution-jwts`\r\n\r\nWhere `--execution-jwts` is a comma-separated list of *file paths*. It must be the same length as the list supplied to `--execution-endpoints`. Each file path matches to the execution-endpoint with the same index (1:1). \r\n\r\n- If `--execution-jwts` present, for each item in the list:\r\n    - If file exists, read it and use it for that EL.\r\n    - If the file doesn't exist, create a new file with a random secret and use it for that EL.\r\n- If `--execution-jwts` is not present:\r\n    - If a file at the default path exists, read it and use that token for all ELs.\r\n    - If a file does not exist and the default path, create one and use that token for all ELs.\r\n    \r\n",
